  10 class RequirementsTXTUpdater(object):
  11 
  12     SUB_REGEX = r"^{}(?=\s*\r?\n?$)"
  13 
  14     @classmethod
  15     def update(cls, content, dependency, version, spec="==", hashes=()):
  16         """
  17         Updates the requirement to the latest version for the given content and adds hashes
  18         if neccessary.
  19         :param content: str, content
  20         :return: str, updated content
  21         """
  22         new_line = "{name}{spec}{version}".format(name=dependency.full_name, spec=spec, version=version)
  23         appendix = ''
  24         # leave environment markers intact
  25         if ";" in dependency.line:
  26             # condense multiline, split out the env marker, strip comments and --hashes
  27             new_line += ";" + dependency.line.splitlines()[0].split(";", 1)[1] \
  28                 .split("#")[0].split("--hash")[0].rstrip()
  29         # add the comment
  30         if "#" in dependency.line:
  31             # split the line into parts: requirement and comment
  32             parts = dependency.line.split("#")
  33             requirement, comment = parts[0], "#".join(parts[1:])
  34             # find all whitespaces between the requirement and the comment
  35             whitespaces = (hex(ord('\t')), hex(ord(' ')))
  36             trailing_whitespace = ''
  37             for c in requirement[::-1]:
  38                 if hex(ord(c)) in whitespaces:
  39                     trailing_whitespace += c
  40                 else:
  41                     break
  42             appendix += trailing_whitespace + "#" + comment
  43         # if this is a hashed requirement, add a multiline break before the comment
  44         if dependency.hashes and not new_line.endswith("\\"):
  45             new_line += " \\"
  46         # if this is a hashed requirement, add the hashes
  47         if hashes:
  48             for n, new_hash in enumerate(hashes):
  49                 new_line += "\n    --hash={method}:{hash}".format(
  50                     method=new_hash['method'],
  51                     hash=new_hash['hash']
  52                 )
  53                 # append a new multiline break if this is not the last line
  54                 if len(hashes) > n + 1:
  55                     new_line += " \\"
  56         new_line += appendix
  57 
  58         regex = cls.SUB_REGEX.format(re.escape(dependency.line))
  59 
  60         return re.sub(regex, new_line, content, flags=re.MULTILINE)
  61

  76 class PipfileUpdater(object):
  77     @classmethod
  78     def update(cls, content, dependency, version, spec="==", hashes=()):
  79         data = toml.loads(content)
  80         if data:
  81             for package_type in ['packages', 'dev-packages']:
  82                 if package_type in data:
  83                     if dependency.full_name in data[package_type]:
  84                         data[package_type][dependency.full_name] = "{spec}{version}".format(
  85                             spec=spec, version=version
  86                         )
  87         try:
  88             from pipenv.project import Project
  89         except ImportError:
  90             raise ImportError("Updating a Pipfile requires the pipenv extra to be installed. Install it with "
  91                               "pip install dparse[pipenv]")
  92         pipfile = tempfile.NamedTemporaryFile(delete=False)
  93         p = Project(chdir=False)
  94         p.write_toml(data=data, path=pipfile.name)
  95         data = open(pipfile.name).read()
  96         os.remove(pipfile.name)
  97         return data

 100 class PipfileLockUpdater(object):
 101     @classmethod
 102     def update(cls, content, dependency, version, spec="==", hashes=()):
 103         data = json.loads(content)
 104         if data:
 105             for package_type in ['default', 'develop']:
 106                 if package_type in data:
 107                     if dependency.full_name in data[package_type]:
 108                         data[package_type][dependency.full_name] = {
 109                             'hashes': [
 110                                 "{method}:{hash}".format(
 111                                     hash=h['hash'],
 112                                     method=h['method']
 113                                 ) for h in hashes
 114                             ],
 115                             'version': "{spec}{version}".format(
 116                                 spec=spec, version=version
 117                             )
 118                         }
 119         return json.dumps(data, indent=4, separators=(',', ': ')) + "\n"
